16:37:42 INFO gaia_agent.nodes.executor: [executor] calling tool=run_python args={'code': 'import requests\nfrom bs4 import BeautifulSoup\n\ndef get_wikipedia_content(title):\n    headers = {\'User-Agent\': \'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36\'}\n    url = f"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/{title.replace(\' \', \'_\')}"\n    response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)\n    if response.status_code == 200:\n        return response.text\n    return None\n\n# Check for discography page first\ndiscography_html = get_wikipedia_content("Mercedes Sosa discography")\nif discography_html:\n    print("Found \'Mercedes Sosa discography\' page.")\n    soup = BeautifulSoup(discography_html, \'html.parser\')\nelse:\n    print("\'Mercedes Sosa discography\' page not found. Checking main page.")\n    main_html = get_wikipedia_content("Mercedes_Sosa")\n    soup = BeautifulSoup(main_html, \'html.parser\')\n\n# Find the studio albums section\n# Typically headings are <h2> or <h3>\nstudio_albums = []\nfound_section = False\n\nfor tag in soup.find_all([\'h2\', \'h3\', \'ul\', \'table\']):\n    if tag.name in [\'h2\', \'h3\']:\n        header_text = tag.get_text().lower()\n        if \'studio albums\' in header_text or \'discography\' in header_text:\n            found_section = True\n        elif found_section and (\'live\' in header_text or \'compilation\' in header_text or \'awards\' in header_text):\n            # Stop if we hit another section\n            break\n    elif found_section and tag.name == \'ul\':\n        for li in tag.find_all(\'li\'):\n            text = li.get_text()\n            studio_albums.append(text)\n    elif found_section and tag.name == \'table\':\n        # Many discographies use tables\n        rows = tag.find_all(\'tr\')\n        for row in rows:\n            cells = row.find_all([\'td\', \'th\'])\n            row_text = " | ".join([cell.get_text(strip=True) for cell in cells])\n            studio_albums.append(row_text)\n\nfor album in studio_albums:\n    print(album)\n'}
