16:38:17 INFO gaia_agent.nodes.executor: [executor] calling tool=run_python args={'code': 'import random\nfrom collections import Counter\n\ndef simulate_game(num_balls=100):\n    balls_on_ramp = list(range(4, num_balls + 1))\n    platform = [1, 2, 3]\n    ejected_balls = []\n    \n    while platform:\n        piston = random.randint(1, 3)\n        \n        # Adjust for 0-indexed platform\n        idx = piston - 1\n        \n        # If piston fires at a position where there is no ball, stop or skip?\n        # The prompt implies the platform is filled until ramp is empty.\n        # But if the platform has fewer than 3 balls at the very end, we should handle it.\n        # However, the rules describe transitions based on 3 positions.\n        \n        if idx >= len(platform):\n            # This case shouldn\'t happen based on the prompt "three balls on the platform at a time"\n            # and the ramp logic, but just in case:\n            break\n\n        ejected_ball = platform[idx]\n        ejected_balls.append(ejected_ball)\n        \n        if piston == 1:\n            # Ball at pos 1 ejected.\n            # pos 2 -> pos 1, pos 3 -> pos 2, next ball -> pos 3\n            new_platform = []\n            if len(platform) > 1:\n                new_platform.append(platform[1])\n            if len(platform) > 2:\n                new_platform.append(platform[2])\n            if balls_on_ramp:\n                new_platform.append(balls_on_ramp.pop(0))\n            platform = new_platform\n            \n        elif piston == 2:\n            # Ball at pos 2 ejected. pos 1 rolls away.\n            # pos 3 -> pos 1, next two balls -> pos 2, pos 3\n            new_platform = []\n            if len(platform) > 2:\n                new_platform.append(platform[2])\n            for _ in range(2):\n                if balls_on_ramp:\n                    new_platform.append(balls_on_ramp.pop(0))\n            platform = new_platform\n            \n        elif piston == 3:\n            # Ball at pos 3 ejected. pos 1 rolls away.\n            # pos 2 -> pos 1, next two balls -> pos 2, pos 3\n            new_platform = []\n            if len(platform) > 1:\n                new_platform.append(platform[1])\n            for _ in range(2):\n                if balls_on_ramp:\n                    new_platform.append(balls_on_ramp.pop(0))\n            platform = new_platform\n            \n    return ejected_balls\n\ndef run_monte_carlo(trials=100000):\n    counts = Counter()\n    for _ in range(trials):\n        ejected = simulate_game()\n        counts.update(ejected)\n    return counts\n\nresults = run_monte_carlo(100000)\ntop_ball = results.most_common(1)[0]\nprint(f"Top Ball: {top_ball[0]}, Frequency: {top_ball[1]}")\n\n# Also print top 5 to see if it\'s close\nprint("Top 5 balls:", results.most_common(5))\n'}
